<setup>
  <selectFromSequence name="m" from ="2" to="6"/>
  <selectFromSequence name="n" from ="2" to="5" exclude="$m $m-1 $m+1"/>
  
  <math name="x1">-$m</math>
  <math name="x2">$n</math>
  <math name="y1">-$m</math>
  <math name="y2">$n</math>

  <function name="integrand" variable="y">($m*$n-y^2)/($m-$n) - y</function>
   
  <math name="intValue" simplify>($m*$n^2+$m^2*$n)/($m-$n) - ($n^2-$m^2)/2 - ($n^3+$m^3)/(3*($m-$n))</math>

</setup>  

  <p>
    Consider the curves given by
    <me><math simplify>$m-$n</math>x + y^2 = <math simplify>$m*$n</math>, \ y = x</me>
  </p> 

  <p> 
    <ol marker="a.">
      <li>
        <p>
          Find the exact points of intersection between the curves.  State each intersection point as an ordered pair in the space below; if there is more than one, separate them with commas.  
        </p>
        <p><answer><mathList unordered>($x1,$y1) ($x2,$y2)</mathList></answer></p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>
          State a definite integral whose value is the exact area between the curves.  Note particularly that you need to choose whether to integrate with respect to <m>x</m> or with respect to <m>y</m>; in either case, all of the expressions you enter below should be in a single variable. Enter either <q><m>x</m></q> or <q><m>y</m></q> in the box adjacent to <q><m>d</m></q> to indicate either <q><m>dx</m></q> or <q><m>dy</m></q>.
        </p>
        <p> 
          The area, <m>A</m>, between the curves is given by the definite integral 
        </p>
        <p>
          <m>A = \int_a^b </m> <mathInput name="integrandEntered"/> <m>d</m> <mathInput minWidth="15" name="dWhat"/>
        </p>
        <p>
          where 
          <m>a = </m><mathInput minWidth="30" name="aEntered"/> and <m>b = </m><mathInput minWidth="30" name="bEntered"/>.
          <answer simplifyOnCompare><award><when>$aEntered=$y1 and $bEntered=$y2 and $dWhat = y and $integrandEntered=$integrand </when></award></answer>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Finally, evaluate the integral exactly and report the resulting area, <m>A</m>, below.
        </p>
        <p>
          <m>A = </m><answer>$intValue</answer>
        </p>  
      </li>
    </ol>
  </p>
